rlOspfRouterLsaEntry.description: A single entry from Router LSA.

rlOspfRouterLsaProcessId.name: rlOspfRouterLsaProcessId
rlOspfRouterLsaProcessId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an OSPF process.

rlOspfRouterLsaAreaId.name: rlOspfRouterLsaAreaId
rlOspfRouterLsaAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
rlOspfRouterLsaAreaId.description: The 32 bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

rlOspfRouterLsaLsid.name: rlOspfRouterLsaLsid
rlOspfRouterLsaLsid.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4 Link State ID
rlOspfRouterLsaLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

rlOspfRouterLsaRouterId.name: rlOspfRouterLsaRouterId
rlOspfRouterLsaRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
rlOspfRouterLsaRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

rlOspfRouterLsaIdx.name: rlOspfRouterLsaIdx
rlOspfRouterLsaIdx.description: The index is a unsigned 32-bit integer. It is used as sequence number of entry in the LSA and relevant only for Router or Network LSA which can contain unlimited number of entries.

rlOspfRouterLsaSequence.name: rlOspfRouterLsaSequence
rlOspfRouterLsaSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
rlOspfRouterLsaSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

rlOspfRouterLsaAge.name: rlOspfRouterLsaAge
rlOspfRouterLsaAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

rlOspfRouterLsaChecksum.name: rlOspfRouterLsaChecksum
rlOspfRouterLsaChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

rlOspfRouterLsaLength.name: rlOspfRouterLsaLength
rlOspfRouterLsaLength.description: The lenth in bytes of the LSA. This includes the 20 byte LSA header.

rlOspfRouterLsaBitV.name: rlOspfRouterLsaBitV
rlOspfRouterLsaBitV.description: When set, the router is an endpoint of one or more fully adjacent virtual links having the described area as Transit area (V is for virtual link endpoint).

rlOspfRouterLsaBitE.name: rlOspfRouterLsaBitE
rlOspfRouterLsaBitE.description: When set, the router is an AS boundary router (E is for external).

rlOspfRouterLsaBitB.name: rlOspfRouterLsaBitB
rlOspfRouterLsaBitB.description: When set, the router is an area border router (B is for border).

rlOspfRouterLsaLinks.name: rlOspfRouterLsaLinks
rlOspfRouterLsaLinks.description: The number of router links described in this LSA. This must be the total collection of router links (i.e., interfaces) to the area.

rlOspfRouterLsaLinkID.name: rlOspfRouterLsaLinkID
rlOspfRouterLsaLinkID.description: Identifies the object that this router link connects to. Value depends on the link's Type.

rlOspfRouterLsaLinkData.name: rlOspfRouterLsaLinkData
rlOspfRouterLsaLinkData.description: Value depends on the link's Type field.

rlOspfRouterLsaType.name: rlOspfRouterLsaType
rlOspfRouterLsaType.description: A quick description of the router link.

rlOspfRouterLsaMetric.name: rlOspfRouterLsaMetric
rlOspfRouterLsaMetric.description: The cost of using this router link.
